---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import { CONTACT_INFO } from "../config";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | The Quiet Guardian"
  description="Our commitment to the respectful and secure handling of your family's data."
>
  <Nav />

  <main id="main-content" class="pt-40 pb-32">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8 md:px-12">
      <h1
        class="text-4xl md:text-5xl mb-12"
        style="font-family: var(--font-headline); color: var(--on-surface);"
      >
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>

      <div
        class="prose prose-stone max-w-none space-y-8"
        style="color: var(--on-surface-variant);"
      >
        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            1. Controller Identity
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            The Quiet Guardian ("we," "us," or "our") is the data controller for
            the personal information collected through this website. We are
            registered in Ireland.<br /><br />
            <strong>Business Address:</strong>
            {CONTACT_INFO.businessAddress}, Ireland<br />
            <strong>Contact:</strong>
            <a
              href="mailto:care@quietguardian.com"
              style="color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline;"
              >care@quietguardian.com</a
            >
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            2. Legal Basis for Processing
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We process your personal data under the following legal bases:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>
              <strong>Contractual Necessity:</strong> To provide the professional
              assessment and restoration services you request.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Legitimate Interests:</strong> To respond to inquiries and improve
              our preservation services.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have explicitly opted in to specific
              communications or data uses.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            3. Data We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We only collect the information necessary to provide our
            professional services. This includes:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>
              <strong>Contact Details:</strong> Name, email address, and phone number.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Site Details:</strong> Cemetery name, section/plot numbers,
              and names on memorials.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Geographic Data:</strong> GPS coordinates provided via our interactive
              map.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            4. Third-Party Processors
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We use a limited number of trusted third-party services to operate
            our business:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>
              <strong>Formspree:</strong> To securely process and deliver your assessment
              requests to our team.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Plausible Analytics:</strong> For privacy-friendly website analytics
              that do not use cookies or collect personal data.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            5. Data Retention
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to fulfil
            the purposes for which it was collected, including for the purposes
            of satisfying any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
            Typically, inquiry data is held for 24 months unless a service
            contract is initiated.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            6. Your Data Rights
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            Under the GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your
            personal data:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mt-4">
            <li>
              <strong>Right to Access:</strong> Request a copy of the data we hold
              about you.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> Request that we correct inaccurate
              or incomplete data.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> Request that we delete your data
              ("right to be forgotten").
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Right to Portability:</strong> Request a transfer of your data
              to another service.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Right to Object:</strong> Object to our processing of your data
              based on legitimate interests.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2
            class="text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4"
            style="color: var(--primary);"
          >
            7. Right to Lodge a Complaint
          </h2>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">
            If you believe we have not handled your data correctly, you have the
            right to lodge a complaint with the Data Protection Commission
            (DPC), the Irish supervisory authority for data protection issues (<a
              href="https://www.dataprotection.ie"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              style="color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline;"
              >www.dataprotection.ie</a
            >).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="pt-8 border-t border-outline-variant/20">
          <p class="text-sm italic">
            Last Updated: April 2026<br />
            For any privacy-related inquiries, please contact <a
              href="mailto:care@quietguardian.com"
              style="color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline;"
              >care@quietguardian.com</a
            >
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
